Sep 2 2008 	Great Location on 'The Strip' With Only A Few Minor Quirks	Polo Towers was just what we needed while staying in Vegas. The rooms were very, very clean, but had a few minor quirks. One of the biggest quirks to me was that the a/c wouldn't go below 70 degrees! Most people that I know...that are staying in Vegas when it's 100+ outside would like for the air to go below 70 to keep you cool! I called the front desk and they said it 'was automatically set not to go below 70'. They didn't give me a reason, so I assume it is to cut costs. In other words...if you are a person that needs lots of cool air, this may not be the place for you! Also, in the suite attached to the main room the bed was surprisingly comfortable (for a fold out), but the a/c was a bit noisy and our sliding shower door kept getting off the tracks. My husband had to put it back on several times. None of these things were major issues for us though. Overall though, the rooms were very nice and well appointed with granite countertops, flat screen t.v.'s and nice furniture. Our view of The Strip on the 16th floor was great! I spent one afternoon at the pool which was very nice. They had very nice furniture at the pool along with cabanas to provide some shade. However, the pool seemed a bit small to me for all of the people that were in it (however, this was Labor Day weekend, so keep that in mind). It's not a 'swimming pool' per se, but more of a wading pool. It's only about 3.5 feet deep. It's mostly just to keep you cool. It's great if you are wanting to sit in the pool and read a book or just have a drink and relax. There is also a nice jacuzzi by the pool which I did not use. The pool was nice, but did seem that it could stand to be cleaned a little. Overall, the pool area was a great place to relax.One thing I really liked about this hotel was that there was NO CASINO in it. I truly enjoy going to casinos, but don't want one where I am sleeping. This made sleeping much more enjoyable and less noisy. The Monte Carlo and NY NY are across the street, so gambling is easily accessible. Also, Walgreens and CVS are close by along with a couple of beer/liquor stores. Advice from me = if you are a drinker stock up on beer/wine at the stores around the corner from Polo Towers. It's MUCH cheaper than buying drinks out at bars, etc. for 11$ a drink...ouch! With a full kitchen in the room it's easy to keep beverages on hand.One thing to note while you are at Polo Towers is that they are VERY strict about what time you check out. They do not allow late check out and if you don't check out on time they charge you double the room rate...so, don't oversleep! Overall, this was a great place to stay if you are looking for some peace and quiet in the midst of all of the craziness on &quot;The Strip&quot;. Polo Towers was a nice retreat at the end of the day or for a nap before going out in the evenings. Enjoy your trip to Vegas!	
