Apr 7 2008 	Your room depends on who owns in...	Even if you book through a hotel booking site, you may or may not be renting someone's time-share unit.In our case, we were renting a time-share unit, which was totally fine by us. The rate was reasonable, and the location was fine - not right on the strip, but just off. It was a studio with Murphy Bed. With the bed up, there were some cushions that formed a couch for seating 2-3 people. With the bed down, well, seating was on the bed. Room was quite small but we knew that going in - suitable for maximum 2 persons. You could squeeze 3 people on the bed and have a 4th sleep on the pile of cushions on the floor (as we did one night when a couple friends surprised us), but it's definitely not recommended (and may violate your agreement). Nice balcony with views (though view depends on what side you're on). Room was very clean and had pretty much everything you'd want for a weekend get-away: mini-fridge, small kitchenette with plates etc, full bath, TV, CD player, DVD player, radio.  On-site mini-mart had anything you might have forgotten at home, plenty of other shops nearby. Took forever to get a taxi to show up, at any time of day. Again - your experience will vary with whomever owns the room, but in general it seemed the property was well-kept.	
Mar 30 2008 	Disappointing Polo Towers	We just returned from a five night stay at Polo Towers. I thought we wre in for a treat by most of the reviews, but the hotel was a big disappointment. The first two room suite was very dirty. There was body fluid all over the couch and chair. The hotel offered to clean it for us, but we wanted another room. We were told that all rooms from the seventh floor up had been updated. This was not the case. Our second two bedroom suite had very old and broken furniture. The kitchen and bath countertops had been updated as well as the lights. That was all that we could tell that was fairly new. The view was great, but the hotel is right behind the Polynesian Village. It is loud All night. We were on a non-smoking floor so we thought we would be safe from smoke. The studio side of our suite, had the smell of cigarette smoke floating through all the time. We could not use the bed on that side and had to keep the ajoining door closed to keep out the smoke. My son had to sleep on the couch! When we checked out we asked for the front desk to call a cab and the person did not know how to do it. Finally, someone said that he would call and fifteen minutes later, we asked where the cab was. Another person told us that cabs rarely come back to this hotel unless dropping someone else off. We were told to go to Planet Hollywood Casino and grab a taxi there. We were very disappointed with our experience at this Diamond Resort and will not be back.	
