Mar 5 2008 	Nice 2 BD Suite	I like to write reviews of the places we have stayed in order for others to read before booking a trip because I read TA for the same reason. We booked 3 nights-4 days at the Polo Towers using my parents timeshare. My mother was celebrating her 67th birthday. The Polo Towers are very clean and the staff were also very nice. I'm not a fan of the location but once the City Center is completed and hopefully they get rid to the 2 strip malls out front, the place would be much better. The strip malls out front attract an undesirable crowd but we just didn't let it bother us too much since we drove most of the time.We had a 2 bedroom suite which is actually a 1 bedroom suite with an attached jr. suite for the 2nd bedroom. We were given a room overlooking the strip on the 14th floor right near the elevator. (We were exciting that we didn't have to walk the south 40 from the elevator). The rooms were one of the remodeled rooms and the decor was really nice with granite counter tops, and the colors were rich golds and browns. My parents stayed in the 1 bedroom suite side and my husband and I stayed in the jr. suite side. The jr. suite side had a separate entrance, small kitchenette with microwave, coffee maker, sink, and refrigerator. Bring your own coffee as they only provide one small sampler for your coffee maker. Also we had a hugh balconey and a hugh shower. There was only one sink and with the hugh shower the bath was small. (I wouldn't recommend a long term stay in just the jr. suite since it is a little small but with the attached 1 bedroom it was a hugh apartment). The 1 bedroom suite had a full kitchen with everything including a full size refrigerator and dishwasher. All utensils, plates, cups, etc are included. They provide shuttle service to the grocery store if you don't have a car. All in all the Polo Towers were nice (didn't check out the pool areas). It was a comfortable stay and I would stay again.	
Feb 19 2008	Viva LV	We stayed, my wife and myself in the Villas, Tower III, the week of Feb1-8. We had a one bedroom villa on the ninth floor, with a living room, kitchen, and dining area which seats 4. We rented an adjoining studio, with murphy bed and mini kitchen for my brother and his wife. The combination 2 bedroom, 2 bath unit was more than large enough for the 4 of us. We watched the Super Bowl on the large screen plasma TV in the living room. Each bedroom also had TV's. Our bathroom had two vanities, a stall shower and a jacuzzi tub. The other bathroom had a walk in shower. All the counters were granite, and the tile work in the kitchen and bathrooms was definitely Tuscan in design. The adjoining halls on the 9th floor of Towers I &amp; II were being renovated while we were there. I snooped in there every day and was amazed by the amount of work they got done in a week. But, while the improvements looked good, they did not look in design like Tower III. The tile work is fine, but not fancy like in the Villas. But the improvement over the older suites is dramatic.  Polo is a short walk to Planet Hollywood (formally the Alladin), and the new Marriott shares parking with the Polo Towers. We declined an offer to tour the Marriott and go to a Polo Towers owners mtg (we recently bought this unit as a resale), and nobody bothered us for the rest of the week. We went to 3 shows: Zumanity (at New York New York) which I would skip as it didn't compare to other cirques we've been to; The Producers (at Paris) and the FabFour (at Sharara), which we both loved.The City Center being built across the street(Strip) is going to be huge!! We had a good look at it from our dining room window.	
Jan 6 2008 	Excellent Location	All in all we found our stay at the Polo Towers very pleasant - the location was excellent, a very central spot on the strip and easy access to everything. The rooms were clean and comfortable, staff very friendly and the concierge was always more than helpful. Not the best hotel if you want all the glitz and glam of Las Vegas in your hotel (this is basically just a hotel, no shops, casino or anything on the complex) but all we wanted was a room to stay in as all casinos, shops etc in the other hotels were easily accessible and most places within walking distance - if not just a short bus ride away.	
