Sep 22 2007	Newly renovated spacious accommodations	With another couple we stayed in a two bedroom suite. We asked for one of the newly renovated ones when we checked in (they are renovating all of them, floor by floor). The suite was beautiful and clean with a view of the strip. The kitchen was fully equipped and even had a coffee pack for the coffee maker. The dining table was next to a huge window with a view of the strip. The sofa and chairs in the living room were comfortable. We did not use the sleeper sofa, but the apt can sleep six. You can get a one bedroom studio with a comfortable Murphy bed and a microwave and small refrigerator, a one bedroom with the kitchen and dining/living room area or a two bedroom which is both bedrooms together (the apts are lockout). Each bedroom has its own bathroom.The maid service, which was supposed to be once a week, took out garbage every day and left a fresh coffee pack every day. They also gave us fresh towels. We took advantage of the free parking and rented a car, which we used to take to the supermarket and for driving around the strip. We bought our own liquor and had drinks and h'ordeuvres in the apt before we went out to dinner. We also had breakfast in the suite, saving a lot of money. There is a pool and jacuzzi on the roof. You have to pay for the wi-fi service. it is a short walk to the Aladdin and there is a nice, reasonably priced mall connected to the Aladdin where we found a fine men's store with some real bargains. There is a strip shopping center in front of the hotel with a half price ticket booth where we got tickets to shows and discount dinner tickets. We saved a lot of money staying there, but everything was first class.	
