Aug 28 2007 	Good location and value	The Suites (and Villas) at Polo Towers is a time share. I think it has the best time share location in Las Vegas. It has a Strip address and is across from the Monte Carlo and between the MGM Grand and Planet Hollywood. We exchanged in for a two bedroom with no problem, but we arrived late and there were no non-smoking, two bedroom suites left. We accepted a one bedroom for the first night and they were able to transfer to a two bedroom the next day without any problem. We were not interested in any of the trips and tours available, but we did use the concierge to book tickets for the Blue Man Group. They handled it well and we even got a complimentary seat upgrade when we arrived at the theater. There was a small convenience store that sold all the basics (no alcohol) at fair prices. There was no gambling on premises. The pool was a rooftop, 22nd floor, 3 feet deep, 20&quot;x50&quot;, family friendly (until 5:00 P.M.) affair with hot tub. There is a separate children's pool. The pool can't compare with those at some of the other resorts, but there were always lounges and cabanas available. We spent most of our time there during the days and enjoyed it. Our suite was large, clean and well-equipped. Staff was friendly and helpful. We checked out at 10:00 A.M., but our shuttle wasn't going to pick us up until 8:10 that night. There was no hospitality room, but we asked for and got courtesy keys for the pool. One problem: it has a Las Vegas Blvd. address, but it is set back a little from the Strip. If you didn't know it was there you might miss it. Access was though a deserted former food court, or down what amounted to alley ways. My wife said she would have felt a little uncomfortable entering or leaving the building alone at night. While there are newer and glitzier time shares in the area, the location means that if I &quot;trade in&quot; again, this would probably be my first choice.	
