May 18 2004	Very classy place	I noticed that most of these reviews are from adult individuals or couples. I can offer the point of view from an 18 year old. I just came back from my trip to Las Vegas, where I stayed at the Polo Towers on the Strip. I went with my family, where my mother and her husband had purchased two bedrooms last year while at a time share presentation. They were offered only this week as a one time deal. This year, they bought a time share at the presentation. My experience at the Polo Towers was pleasant. It is in a wonderful location..right beside the MGM Grand, and in front of the Monte Carlo and New York, New York. It's right on the strip, so it is very convenient when one wants to tour the sites. The rooms were very clean, and we had a great view of the Strip from our balcony and windows. They proclaim that they decorate in a Venetian style, but I didn't really get that impression, it was more just classy than anything. The entrance is quite impressive, with marble floors, a piano playing, and a big monument of horses. All in all, it was very nice, and the people were very welcoming and warm. The only drawback is the pool on the roof, it's only 3 feet deep. My brother (who is 14 yrs old) and I were a bit dissapointed. They do have a nice hot tub sauna though, and these wonderful places to lounge that looked like beds. I would recommend the Polo Towers to anybody who likes quiet luxury and the sound of casinos ommited from their sleep. That was a definite plus!	
May 18 2004	Just bought over the weekend....	We just bought a 2 bedroom timeshare at the Polo Towers over the weekend, and I couldn't be happier. We were drawn in by the free Lance Burton tickets and the fact that my husband and I enjoy touring properties anyway. I was not prepared to fall in love. I don't tend to be easily impressed by sales people, or hotel rooms in general, but I was very pleased at the many ammenities The Polo Towers had to offer, and the fact that they are located in a prime location on the strip. The salesman and his manager were more than cordial to us, and since the presentation cut into both our breakfast and lunch, the manager happily passed his chicken strips and french fries our way. My husband, who is pretty conservative when it comes to money, and is prone to buyers remorse over a pack of gum, is equally happy with our purchase. The biggest selling point for us was the flexibility in the financing and payments. We were able to put only 10% down at signing, 40% due on July 1st, and 12 months of payments that are just $100 per month without any finance charges. We can't wait for our first vacation at The Polo Towers!	
