Mar 23 2004	Information they give you broken down....	Here is the information they give you broken down so you can make your own analysis:Studio or 1 bedroom offered ($24,000 &amp; $28,000 with a &quot;BUY IT NOW Discount of 3,000-8,000 off with more room to &quot;bargain&quot; possible but unlikely) with a true cost closer to $10,000... This was what I was told when I did the &quot;tour&quot; in March of 2004.Now, on top of this you have a yearly fee for (maintenance, taxes, staff, etc) This fee varies depending on the style (studio $595 / 1 bedroom $895) and is paid every year by you...So, using the information that I was given this is how it breaks down (with the &quot;discount&quot; they gave me to try to make me buy):1 bedroom $21,000 with yearly fees of $895 (note: this does not include the other fees to be able to trade your share with others or to participate actively with their other timeshare properties)So, let's assume you will vacation for the next 10 years and want to do it in Las Vegas...21,000 + (8950 = 895*10) = 29,950 for 10 years 2,950 each year or 421.43 each day for seven daysNow, the room is nice and the location is good BUT 421.43 is very high to be locked into for a week in Vegas that you have to bid for...Even at 20 years the yearly/day cost is still high at $1945/$277 year/day...Not to mention the fact of being tied to a bidding system.Now, if you just KNOW when you will be in Vegas to vacation and can buy that week then this might be worth your time, otherwise, just book a good hotel or buy property...Especially since you can't receive any hard information directly from them and if you ask to review some then they will &quot;allow&quot; you to do so but only on site at the time of your &quot;tour&quot;I don't know about you but if I can't review a major purchase overnight and I'm denied any written documentation but only asked to &quot;trust&quot; some total stranger that he or she will act in my best interest---??? I WALK AWAY...Others may feel different but I prefer to gamble with at least a good understanding of the game before jumping blindly in....Hope this helps....joseph_ut@hotmail.com	
